cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.THEORY, cs.MS 

This paper discusses the comparison of different models of object-oriented programming, which falls under the programming languages (cs.PL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO) sub-categories. It also involves the comparison of different theoretical models, which could be categorized under software engineering (cs.SE), theory of computation (cs.THEORY), and mathematical software (cs.MS).
